Press topics fromcustomizationto plugin reviews. With such a large potential as a custom CMS, we feel that no one should limit their WordPress powered website. As expert WordPress developers, we know the tips and tricks to help you move along.<!--more--> Feel free to check back periodically, we\'ll be posting every week! For today, here is our first tip: Adding a WordPress Menu to your theme. This may be useful if you want a footer menu or just a second one for a larger navigation.\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 1)</strong> Open up yourpreferred FTP client and code editor.\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 2)</strong> Navigate to your theme directory. Locate in your template files where you would like to put the newcustom WordPress menu, open your functions.php and your style.css.\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 3)</strong> In your functions.php, paste the following code:\r\n\r\n<?php echo preg_replace(\'%\\r%\', \'\', highlight_string(\"<?php\r\n/** Tell WordPress to run my_theme_setup() when the \'after_setup_theme\' hook is run. */\r\nadd_action( \'after_setup_theme\', \'my_theme_setup\' );\r\nif ( ! function_exists( \'my_theme_setup\' ) ):\r\nfunction my_theme_setup() {\r\n	register_nav_menus( array(\r\n		\'my_menu\' = \'My Custom Menu\',\r\n	) );\r\n}\r\nendif;\r\n?>\", true)); ?>\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 4)</strong> Paste the following code into your templates files where you want your new custom WordPress menu to appear:\r\n\r\n<?php echo preg_replace(\'%\\r%\', \'\', highlight_string(\"<div id=\\\"access\\\" role=\\\"navigation\\\">\r\n<?php wp_nav_menu( array( \'container_class\' => \'menu-header\', \'theme_location\' => \'my_menu\' ) ); ?>\r\n</div><!-- #access -->\", true)); ?>\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 5)</strong> Paste the following code into your stylesheet(style.css) and style to match you theme:\r\n\r\n<?php echo preg_replace(\'%\\r%\', \'\', highlight_string(\"/* =Menu\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------- \r\n-------------------------------------------------------------- */\r\n\r\n#access {\r\n	background: #000;\r\n	display: block;\r\n	float: left;\r\n	margin: 0 auto;\r\n	width: 940px;\r\n	position: relative;\r\n	z-index: 9999;\r\n}\r\n#access a {\r\n	color: #aaa;\r\n	display: block;\r\n	line-height: 38px;\r\n	padding: 0 10px;\r\n	text-decoration: none;\r\n}\r\n#access li:hover > a {\r\n	background: #333;\r\n	color: #fff;\r\n}\r\n#access ul ul a {\r\n	background: #333;\r\n	line-height: 1em;\r\n	padding: 10px;\r\n	width: 160px;\r\n	height: auto;\r\n}\r\n#access ul ul :hover > a {\r\n	background: #333;\r\n	color: #fff;\r\n}\r\n#access ul ul {\r\n	box-shadow: 0px 3px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);\r\n	-moz-box-shadow: 0px 3px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);\r\n	-webkit-box-shadow: 0px 3px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);\r\n	display: none;\r\n	position: absolute;\r\n	top: 38px;\r\n	left: 0;\r\n	float: left;\r\n	width: 180px;\r\n	z-index: 99999;\r\n}\r\n#access ul ul li {\r\n	min-width: 180px;\r\n}\r\n#access ul ul ul {\r\n	left: 100%;\r\n	top: 0;\r\n}\r\n#access ul li.current_page_item > a,\r\n#access ul li.current-menu-ancestor > a,\r\n#access ul li.current-menu-item > a,\r\n#access ul li.current-menu-parent > a,\r\n* html #access ul li.current_page_item a,\r\n* html #access ul li.current-menu-ancestor a,\r\n* html #access ul li.current-menu-item a,\r\n* html #access ul li.current-menu-parent a,\r\n* html #access ul li a:hover {\r\n	color: #fff;\r\n}\r\n#access .menu-header ul,\r\ndiv.menu ul {\r\n	list-style: none;\r\n	margin: 0;\r\n}\r\n#access .menu-header li,\r\ndiv.menu li {\r\n	float: left;\r\n	position: relative;\r\n	margin-bottom: 0;\r\n}\r\n#access ul li:hover > ul {\r\n	display: block;\r\n}\r\n\", true)); ?>\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 6)</strong> Pat yourself on the back for a job well done!\r\n','Hello world!','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-17','','','2012-06-14 18:37:56','2012-06-14 18:37:56','',1,'http://www.markitmedia.com/blog/2012/06/1-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(135,1,'2012-06-27 19:42:14','2012-06-27 19:42:14','At Markit Media, we beli