ck with the ability to recognize a link form many popular video site and use to to automatically embed a player in your post. (Check the \"Auto-embeds\" check box in Administration > Settings > Media SubPanel.)\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Check out this cool video:\r\n\r\n<code>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nTDNLUzjkpg</code>\r\n\r\nThat was a cool video.</blockquote>\r\n\r\nOptionally you can wrap your video link in an &#91;embed&#93; shortcode. Using this shortcode does the same thing, but doesn\'t require the link to be on it\'s own line, and allows you to specify the maximum (but not fixed) size of the video like so:\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n&#91;embed width=\"123\" height=\"456\"&#93;<code>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nTDNLUzjkpg</code>&#91;/embed&#93;\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nWordPress natively supprts video embeds from the following sites:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>YouTube (only public videos and playlists - \"unlisted\" and \"private\" videos will not embed)</li>\r\n	<li>Vimeo</li>\r\n	<li>DailyMotion</li>\r\n	<li>blip.tv</li>\r\n	<li>Flickr (both videos and images)</li>\r\n	<li>Viddler</li>\r\n	<li>Hulu</li>\r\n	<li>Qik</li>\r\n	<li>Revision3</li>\r\n	<li>Scribd</li>\r\n	<li>Photobucket</li>\r\n	<li>PollDaddy</li>\r\n	<li>WordPress.tv (only VideoPress-type videos for the time being)</li>\r\n	<li>SmugMug (WordPress 3.0+)</li>\r\n	<li>FunnyOrDie.com (WordPress 3.0+)</li>\r\n	<li>Twitter (WordPress 3.4+)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nUntil next time, happy video blogging!','Posting Videos in WordPress: a Tutorial','','publish','open','open','','posting-videos-in-wordpress-a-tutorial','','','2012-08-10 16:11:33','2012-08-10 16:11:33','',0,'http://www.markitmedia.com/blog/?p=217',0,'post','',0),(218,1,'2012-07-20 16:18:29','2012-07-20 16:18:29','','Posting Videos in WordPress: a Tutorial','','inherit','open','open','','217-revision','','','2012-07-20 16:18:29','2012-07-20 16:18:29','',217,'http://www.markitmedia.com/blog/2012/07/217-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(21