tomers aware of what you have going on. Not to mention that google loves twitter and indexes your posts very easily and it Free! Also make sure to put a link to your twitter on your website. This is a great two-way link and will help building your rank on google.</li>\r\n \r\n<div><strong>Step 3</strong></div>\r\n<p>Facebook. Facebook has totally revolutionized the social networking environment. What you want to do is build a personal facebook page and a business fan page. Invite everyone and anyone you know; Old schoolmates, old customers, etc. Then you want to invite them to your business page. Include all your business info especially your website and twitter. Also make sure to put a link to your facebook on your website</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step 4</strong></div>\r\n<p>Craigslist. Craigslist has a great services section where you can submit classifieds for your business based on your location. Unfortunately it is very public so you may get a couple spam emails but it\'s well worth it. Make sure to post at least 3 times a day to ensure your at the top of the list in your category.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step 5</strong></div>\r\n<p>Search Engines. Next you need to submit your website to the main search engines like Google and Yahoo. Here is the website to add your url.\r\ngoogle: http://www.google.com/addurl/\r\nyahoo: http://siteexplorer.search.yahoo.com/submit\r\nbing: http://www.bing.com/docs/submit.aspx\r\n\r\nThere are tons of other search engines but these are the most important.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step 6</strong></div>\r\n<p>Article writing. This is by far the best and most effective way to generate traffic to your website and then eventually make you money. You need to write relevant keyword rich articles that you can then link back to your website. Once you write an article make sure to add your URL in the resource box. Here are some of the best article sites to write on.\r\nezinearticles.com\r\nhubpages.com\r\nehow.com\r\nThis is important. Make sure every article is unique. Do not mass submit the same exact article. Article sites and search engines hate this and will probably remove you and impact your traffic very negatively.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step 7</strong></div>\r\n<p>Final step. You need to build back links to your website. You will already have one from twitter, facebook and craigslist but you need more. I use http://www.webconfs.com/backlink-builder.php to help me find relevant back links to my website. All you have to do is put in a keyword that is relevant to you website and it will spit out a ton of sites you can link to. Make sure to only to sign up for one way links or non-reciprocal links. This means that you don\'t have to put their link on your website in order for them to put your link on their site.</p>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.ehow.com/how_5827217_market-home-business.html\" target=_blank>By James Roland</a>','How to Market Your Home Business for Free','','publish','open','open','','how-to-market-your-home-business-for-free','','','2010-07-27 00:31:59','2010-07-27 00:31:59','',0,'http://markitmedia.net/blog/?p=41',0,'post','',214),(42,3,'2010-07-26 22:44:42','2010-07-26 22:44:42','<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p id=\"intelliTxt\">Starting a business from home? Already have a small home based business but don\'t have any customers? Here is a list of things you can do to not only market your small business but do it for free!</p>\n<!-- google_ad_section_end() -->\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\"></script>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>Difficulty: Easy</div>\n<div>Instructions</div>\n</div>\n<!-- google_ad_section_start() -->\n<div>\n<h4>Things You\'ll Need:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Computer</li>\n<li>Time</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<ol id=\"intelliTxt\">\n<li id=\"jsArticleStep1\">\n<div><strong>Step 1</strong></div>\nWebsite. This may seem obvious but you need a website. The technology wave were seeing has made it so affordable to build a website you can\'t do without one. You ca